description: This first "Krystal" release in almost 20 years is this 48 page anthology of stories set in the distant future written by Jaymes Reed and illustrated by Marc Borstel. Included: Krystal's origin, "Dalworth's Daughter", "Club Trip", about a nightclub bombing that makes Krystal re-think her inner "gender war", "Obedient Shackles", the tale of a sex slave rescue attempt and much more!
name: Fire

description: If you remove identity and get to the core of who Peter Parker really is, is he a hero? Would he act as a hero, when presented with the opportunities of a villain? We're about to find out.
Will Spider-Man turn his back on his great responsibility?
Even though Spidey got most of his memory back, he has to hide that fact from The Profit and his goons. PLUS: Two Spider-Men! WHAT?
The Profit goes deep into Spider-Man's mind for some all out psychological warfare! Will any of Spidey's memories survive? Will they all turn against him?

name: The Five faces of Dr. Spectro

description:
This week's Beano features scenes of extreme menacing! So if you suffer from a softie disposition or knocky knees, do not enter!

Inside this week...

  • Minx-tastic Footie action (no biting)!
  • Get the Menace look and join Dennis's squad!
  • Get lost in the Skatepark Skramble!
  • Win awesome prizes!

Plus jokes, pranks and laughs! Get yours now!

Get ready for the World Cup Final with Beanoball! There are no rules... even gnashing is allowed*! Who will come out on top?

There's plenty of other action too...

  • Awesome competitions!
  • Mind-bending puzzles!
  • Brilliant pranks!

At this and more, inside the pages of The Beano! Don't miss it!

*So even Luis Suarez can play!

This week Rory McIlroy is giving Dennis some golfing tips in time for Beanotown's Open Golf Tournament! I hope Rory has remembered to bring a spare pair of laughing pants... in case he gets a hole in one!

What else is happening in Beanotown this week?

  • You could win an iPod Touch!
  • You must save the library from Thesaurus Rex!
  • You can make prank sweets!
  • You can be a dodger!

Don't miss The Beano - the home of jokes, pranks and laughs!

Beanotown is caught up in Commonwealth Games fever this week! Your laugh-muscles will be put to the test in 'The No Common Sense Games'!

Also inside...

  • A LEGO Ultra Agents comp!
  • Make an awesome X-Wing Fighter!
  • All your favourite comic strip stars!

The Beano wins the gold medal for menacing - don't miss it!

What happens when the sun goes down in Riverdale? The fun doesn't stop, that's for sure! Music clubs, nighttime strolls, and slumber parties await you after dark with Archie and friends! Check out this cool 50-page collection of nighttime stories. The best thing of all? This digital exclusive will always be on your screen, so you can read in the dark!
The group of murderous supervillains leaving a bloody trail across California meet the flying man who has been watching them and others. There will be more death to come.
After the big meeting, nothing is the same. New alliances have formed and casualties have been had on both sides. All the while, Gwendolyn plots her next move.

Therese Sorenson and her clones have been hiding out on Jupiters moon Ganymede for a few years, undetected. But a chance encounter at a trading post in the Asteroid Belt leads to the discovery of the Heartbreakers secret base.

Six young warriors are tasked with protecting the mysterious Luminae, a holy creature of Light in exile from those forces of Darkness that would decimate humanity. When one of the warriors disappears, the others know it is the sign of a superior evil soon to arrive. A stylish dark fantasy by the celebrated artist of Naja and Meka.
name: HC
